{
  "texts": [
    "We also feel that this combination could be particularly impactful for spreadsheet developers wishing to leverage LLMs in their end user programming activities.",
    "There have been many attempts to port software engineering principles and techniques to spreadsheets for instance, the use of Data Flow Diagrams (DFDs) and other diagrammatic methods for planning logic and system structure (Rajalingham, 2001; Hermans, 2011; Mireault, 2015), development methodologies tailored for spreadsheet modelling (Grossman & Ozluk, 2010), and even efforts to transform Excel into a structured programming environment, such as Model Master (Paine, 2001 (Paine,, 2005)).",
    "These approaches were motivated by the desire to increase rigor, reduce errors, and improve maintainability.",
    "However, such efforts have historically had mixed uptake.",
    "One must remember that most spreadsheet developers are not trained computing professionals, and nor are they interested in becoming them."
  ]
}